{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id795b45f5-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1065"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1065"},"text":"§ 1065.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Incontestability of right to use mark under certain conditions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Except on a ground for which application to cancel may be filed at any time under paragraphs (3), (5), and (6) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1064"},"text":"section 1064 of this title","children":[],"tail":", and except to the extent, if any, to which the use of a mark registered on the principal register infringes a valid right acquired under the law of any State or Territory by use of a mark or trade name continuing from a date prior to the date of registration under this chapter of such registered mark, the right of the owner to use such registered mark in commerce for the goods or services on or in connection with which such registered mark has been in continuous use for five consecutive years subsequent to the date of such registration and is still in use in commerce, shall be incontestable: "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided","children":[],"tail":", That—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id795b45f6-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1065/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" there has been no final decision adverse to the owner’s claim of ownership of such mark for such goods or services, or to the owner’s right to register the same or to keep the same on the register; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id795b45f7-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1065/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" there is no proceeding involving said rights pending in the United States Patent and Trademark Office or in a court and not finally disposed of; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id795b45f8-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1065/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" an affidavit is filed with the Director within one year after the expiration of any such five-year period setting forth those goods or services stated in the registration on or in connection with which such mark has been in continuous use for such five consecutive years and is still in use in commerce, and other matters specified in paragraphs (1) and (2) hereof; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id795b45f9-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1065/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" no incontestable right shall be acquired in a mark which is the generic name for the goods or services or a portion thereof, for which it is registered.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"Subject to the conditions above specified in this section, the incontestable right with reference to a mark registered under this chapter shall apply to a mark registered under the Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1881-03-03"},"text":"March 3, 1881","children":[],"tail":", or the Act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1905-02-20"},"text":"February 20, 1905","children":[],"tail":", upon the filing of the required affidavit with the Director within one year after the expiration of any period of five consecutive years after the date of publication of a mark under the provisions of subsection (c) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1062"},"text":"section 1062 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"The Director shall notify any registrant who files the above-prescribed affidavit of the filing thereof.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id795b45fa-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-07-05/ch540"},"text":"July 5, 1946, ch. 540","children":[],"tail":", title I, § 15, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/433"},"text":"60 Stat. 433","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/772/s10"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–772, § 10","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-10-09"},"text":"Oct. 9, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/771"},"text":"76 Stat. 771","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/596/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–596, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-01-02"},"text":"Jan. 2, 1975","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/1949"},"text":"88 Stat. 1949","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/247/s10"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–247, § 10","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-08-27"},"text":"Aug. 27, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/320"},"text":"96 Stat. 320","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/667/tI/s116"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–667, title I, § 116","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-11-16"},"text":"Nov. 16, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/3941"},"text":"102 Stat. 3941","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/dB/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4732/b/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, div. B, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4732(b)(1)(B)]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1536"},"text":"113 Stat. 1536","children":[],"tail":", 1501A–583; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/146/s3/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–146, § 3(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-03-17"},"text":"Mar. 17, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/67"},"text":"124 Stat. 67","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/260/dQ/tII/s225/e/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–260, div. Q, title II, § 225(e)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2020-12-27"},"text":"Dec. 27, 2020","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/2207"},"text":"134 Stat. 2207","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id795b45fb-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id795b45fc-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id795b45fd-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Acts ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1881-03-03"},"text":"March 3, 1881","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1905-02-20"},"text":"February 20, 1905","children":[],"tail":", referred to in text, are acts "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1881-03-03/ch138"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1881, ch. 138","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/21/502"},"text":"21 Stat. 502","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1905-02-20/ch592"},"text":"Feb. 20, 1905, ch. 592","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/33/724"},"text":"33 Stat. 724","children":[],"tail":", which were repealed insofar as inconsistent with this chapter by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-07-05/ch540/s46/a"},"text":"act July 5, 1946, ch. 540, § 46(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/444"},"text":"60 Stat. 444","children":[],"tail":". Act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1905-02-20"},"text":"Feb. 20, 1905","children":[],"tail":", was classified to sections 81 to 109 of this title."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id795b45fe-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2020—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/260"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–260","children":[],"tail":" substituted “paragraphs (3), (5), and (6)” for “paragraphs (3) and (5)” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2010—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/146/s3/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–146, § 3(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “right of the owner” for “right of the registrant” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/146/s3/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–146, § 3(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", amended par. (1) generally. Prior to amendment, par. (1) read as follows: “there has been no final decision adverse to registrant’s claim of ownership of such mark for such goods or services, or to registrant’s right to register the same or to keep the same on the register; and”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/146/s3/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–146, § 3(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “United States” before “Patent and Trademark Office”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1999—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Director” for “Commissioner” in par. (3) and in two places in concluding provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/667"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–667","children":[],"tail":", in introductory provisions, substituted “paragraphs (3) and (5)” for “subsections (c) and (e)”, in par. (3) “paragraphs” for “subsections”, and in par. (4) “the generic name for the goods or services or a portion thereof, for which it is registered” for “the common descriptive name of any article or substance, patented or otherwise”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1982—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/247"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–247","children":[],"tail":" substituted “registration” for “the publication” in provision preceding par. (1)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1975—Par. (2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/596"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–596","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Patent and Trademark Office” for “Patent Office”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1962—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/772"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–772","children":[],"tail":" substituted “(c) and (e) of section 1064” for “(c) and (d) of section 1064” in provision preceding par. (1), and struck out “or trade name” after “in a mark” in par. (4)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id795b45ff-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Rela